<br>
I don't think Mana Burn should have it's ratio increased.  A maximum burn of 10k damage is adequete, especially if there is a chance for criticals due to the Fury line.  I do think that as a Wizard gains levels and a very large mana pool, thereby surpassing the potential to do a 10k blast IF there wasn't a maximum damage cap, there should still be the 10k maximum but should deliver that 10k damage nearly 100% of the time.  I.E. if someone has a mana pool of 5k mana, they will be practically GUARANTEED a 10k burn, because if there wasn't a cap on the maximum damage they would have potentially been able to burn for 12500!  I am not sure if this is how the ability is working currently anyways, honestly...but if it isn't I think it should be.<br>
<br>
The idea of a Mana regenation recourse effect being added to the ability is a good one, but I think it may simply be a better solution to just make it so that the ability ITSELF is relatively weak, but can be amplified by purchasing OTHER AA abilities.  SK HT is not only imfluenced by SCF, some of their other AA abilities make their HT a GUARANTEED critical strike.<br>
<br>
I think if they simply allowed Mana burn to be able to be amplified by other AA abilities, it would be balanced and worth training eventually.<br>
<br>
A new AA ability I would also like to see added is simply one that increases DD damage (as a passive, &quot;stackable&quot; focus effect) by 1% per level trained.  If they wanted to require more points to be spent for more diversity they could have the ability only amplify the damage of a certain &quot;type&quot; of DD, I.E. Fire based, Magic Based, Ice based...<br>
<br>
An AA ability like that would help make another ability like Mana Burn worth having.<br>
<br>
Producing an upgrade to Mana Burn which makes it super powerful again simply isn't going to happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ruldarswiftnote>Ruldar Swiftnote</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/15/03 11:55:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25966.topic&index=42>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Planar Manaburn</span><hr size=1> When I first saw Raystonn's comment about manasong not being normal for a DPS fight, I was quite inclined to respond and correct it.  But, instead I have to say its nice to know that most wizards (or at least the ones that have posted in response defending the use of manasong) know at least something about what a bard can do.<br>
